title: Kunwara
subTitle: Raju and Urmila fall deeply in love and vow to reunite in India. However, complications arise when Raju agrees to pose as Sharmila's husband before her family.

title: Humse Badhkar Kaun
subTitle: Two brothers, a villager and a petty but cunning fraud, help their estranged mother, the chief minister of the state, to oust her enemies and terrorists.

title: Bal Ganesh 3
subTitle: Dhoti, Topi and Suit Boot are more than happy to oblige when a group of alien kids come over to listen to adventure stories about their favourite Bal Ganesh.

title: Ram Avtar
subTitle: Childhood friends Ram and Avtar face a love triangle when Ram falls for Sangeeta, whom Avtar also loves. Ram sacrifices his love for Avtar, but their enemy Gundappaswami threatens to expose the truth.

title: Saajan
subTitle: Breaking conventional barriers, a poor, disabled orphan befriends the son of a wealthy businessman. However, their friendship is put to the test after both friends fall in love with the same woman.

title: Raj Kumar
subTitle: Rajkumar's mother sets out to oppose his marriage after she finds out that he plans to marry the rival kingdom's princess.

title: Dil Hai Tumhaara
subTitle: Sarita raises Shalu, her spouse's love child, and her daughter, Nimmi, but she does not forgive Shalu's past. When she discovers that Shalu is growing close to Nimmi's lover, things become worse.

title: Vishwatma
subTitle: A policeman and a reformed criminal go to Kenya to comprehend a syndicate leader. However, they must break the rules of the land defended by Surya Pratap, a Kenyan police inspector.

title: Yeshwant
subTitle: Yeshwant, an honest police inspector, is framed and arrested for a murder. However, after being released from prison, he learns that his wife is having an affair.

title: Yeshwant
subTitle: Yeshwant, an honest police inspector, is framed and arrested for a murder. However, after being released from prison, he learns that his wife is having an affair.

title: D-Day
subTitle: Intelligence officer Wali Khan and a team of highly-trained officers are set to nab Goldman, one of India's most wanted terrorists. However, their mission is threatened by a minor miscalculation.

title: Gippi
subTitle: Gippi, an overweight teenager, struggles to handle the physical and social changes that come with her age. Soon, she learns to let go of her insecurities and love herself for exactly who she is.

title: Pyar Ke Do Pal
subTitle: Twins Sunil and Anil try to reunite their parents who separated many years ago due to a tragic misunderstanding regarding a friend's wish to have an abortion.

title: Devdas
subTitle: After his wealthy family prohibits him from marrying the woman he is in love with, Devdas's life spirals downward as he takes up alcohol and a life of vice to alleviate the pain.

title: Suhagan
subTitle: Janki's life changes when she leaves her obsolete married life and runs away with Murli. However, trouble ensues when Murli commits suicide.

title: Kuch Kuch Hota Hai
subTitle: After reading the letter her mother had written for her before she died, Anjali decides to bring together her widowed father, Rahul, with his true love who is also named Anjali.

title: Raja Hindustani
subTitle: Raja, a taxi driver, falls in love with Aarti, a rich girl and marries her against her parents' wishes. Later, her stepmother tries to create differences between the couple.

title: Karishma Kali Kaa
subTitle: A devout young woman is falsely accused of murdering a priest and absconding with the temple jewels. With her fate hanging in the balance, the woman seeks divine intervention to prove her innocence.

title: Karishma Kali Kaa
subTitle: A devout young woman is falsely accused of murdering a priest and absconding with the temple jewels. With her fate hanging in the balance, the woman seeks divine intervention to prove her innocence.

title: Ek Ajnabee
subTitle: Former army officer Suryaveer is tasked with protecting a girl, Anamika, whom he dislikes at first but eventually gets attached to. However, when she gets kidnapped, he must find a way to save her.

title: A Wednesday!
subTitle: Prakash Rathod, a retired police commissioner recounts the most memorable case of his career wherein he was informed about a bomb scare in Mumbai by an ordinary commoner.

title: Kasam
subTitle: Kisna, a police officer, goes undercover in a village to expose a drug ring. He manages to convince the villagers to surrender but things take a turn when the police guns down the villagers.

title: Jamai Raja
subTitle: When the wealthy Durgeshwari's daughter falls in love with Raja, a poor boy, she reluctantly agrees to their union. However, she constantly tries to sabotage their relationship, but Raja outwits her.

title: Meri Jung
subTitle: Deepak Verma lives happily with his family, but things change when he is prosecuted by Thakral for murder. His son, Arun, vows to exact revenge against Thakral and prove his father's innocence.

title: Rishtey
subTitle: A man marries his lover and has a child with her against the wishes of her wealthy father. However, his scheming father-in-law ruins their marriage and leaves to care for his boy by himself.

title: Ishq
subTitle: Ranjit and Harbanslal, two rich businessmen, hatch a malicious plan when they discover that their children have fallen in love with individuals from the poorer sections of society.

title: Izzatdaar
subTitle: When Brahm Dutt, a wealthy businessman, is falsely convicted on murder charges, he enlists the help of a boy to exact revenge on Indrajeet, his cruel son-in-law and the cause of all his miseries.
